    • Method Detail

      • zeroCapacityQueue

        public static <T> ReservablePollingQueue<T> zeroCapacityQueue()
        Returns a queue to which no elements can be added, and will never contain any elements.

        The returned list is serializable.

        Thread safety

        The returned queue is safe to be used by multiple threads concurrently.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the hypothetical elements of the return queue
        Returns:
        a zero capacity queue. This method never returns null.

      • createFifoQueue

        public static <T> ReservablePollingQueue<T> createFifoQueue(int maxCapacity)
        Returns an empty queue with the given maximum capacity and FIFO retrieving order.

        This method is effectively equivalent to calling createFifoQueue(maxCapacity, maxCapacity).

        The returned list is serializable.

        Thread safety

        The returned queue may not be used concurrently from multiple threads. If such access is needed, the access must be externally synchronized.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the elements the returned queue can store
        Parameters:
        maxCapacity - the maximum elements the returned queue may hold. This argument must be greater than or equal to zero.
        Returns:
        an empty FIFO queue with the given maximum capacity. This method never returns null.

        public static <T> ReservablePollingQueue<T> createFifoQueue(int maxCapacity,
                                                            int initialQueueCapacity)
        Returns an empty queue with the given maximum capacity and FIFO retrieving order.

        The returned list is serializable.

        Thread safety

        The returned queue may not be used concurrently from multiple threads. If such access is needed, the access must be externally synchronized.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the elements the returned queue can store
        Parameters:
        maxCapacity - the maximum elements the returned queue may hold. This argument must be greater than or equal to zero.
        initialQueueCapacity - an initial capacity the returned queue should reserve initially. Setting this parameter to any allowed value is only an optimization and carry no defined semantics. This argument must be greater than or equal to zero, but no greater than maxCapacity.
        Returns:
        an empty FIFO queue with the given maximum capacity. This method never returns null.

      • createOrderedQueue

        public static <T> ReservablePollingQueue<T> createOrderedQueue(int maxCapacity,
                                                               java.util.Comparator<? super T> comparator)
        Returns an empty queue with the given maximum capacity and with the ordering defined by the given Comparator. The head of the queue is the least element as defined by the comparator.

        This method is effectively equivalent to calling createOrderedQueue(maxCapacity, maxCapacity, comparator).

        The returned list is serializable.

        Thread safety

        The returned queue may not be used concurrently from multiple threads. If such access is needed, the access must be externally synchronized.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the elements the returned queue can store
        Parameters:
        maxCapacity - the maximum elements the returned queue may hold. This argument must be greater than or equal to zero.
        comparator - the comparator defining the order of the returned queue. Can be null, which means using the natural ordering of the elements (i.e., the elements must implement Comparable.
        Returns:
        an empty LIFO queue with the given maximum capacity. This method never returns null.

        public static <T> ReservablePollingQueue<T> createOrderedQueue(int maxCapacity,
                                                               int initialQueueCapacity,
                                                               java.util.Comparator<? super T> comparator)
        Returns an empty queue with the given maximum capacity and with the ordering defined by the given Comparator. The head of the queue is the least element as defined by the comparator.

        The returned list is serializable.

        Thread safety

        The returned queue may not be used concurrently from multiple threads. If such access is needed, the access must be externally synchronized.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the elements the returned queue can store
        Parameters:
        maxCapacity - the maximum elements the returned queue may hold. This argument must be greater than or equal to zero.
        initialQueueCapacity - an initial capacity the returned queue should reserve initially. Setting this parameter to any allowed value is only an optimization and carry no defined semantics. This argument must be greater than or equal to zero, but no greater than maxCapacity.
        comparator - the comparator defining the order of the returned queue. Can be null, which means using the natural ordering of the elements (i.e., the elements must implement Comparable.
        Returns:
        an empty LIFO queue with the given maximum capacity. This method never returns null.
